comments: I really enjoyed this course,however, I feel that some of the methodologies were geared towards forestry alone and were not relevant to other practices.
The professor was very receptive to the feedback, comments and questions of the student, and it was very helpful to the understanding of the course material
Professor Gregoire taught this course in a very easy to understand and beneficial way. I really appreciated the personal feel of this course.
The small size of the class made it a conductive learning environment.

comments: It provides a very firm statistical grounding for future purposes of sampling design beyond just forestry and environmental sciences. I am headed for work in the civil service, and the sampling techniques and designs introduced are a good primer to spur interest in further methodology.
provides technical skills to support research

comments: I felt that this course would force me to think about sampling as i design my own research project.
